6. "What Am I Missing?" (v3 Update)
The intelligence module is impressive but opaque. Cost Intelligence correlates cost spikes with DDL/grant/task changes — but there's no confidence score on the correlation. Users need to know "how sure are you this change caused the spike?" A statistical correlation without a confidence interval is an assertion, not intelligence.

Forecast without anomaly boundaries. The run-rate projection shows a linear projection but (from what I can see) doesn't show confidence intervals or anomaly bands. Finance teams expect upper/lower bounds, not a single number.

The summary autoload budget is 1 — but is 1 enough? For sections like DBA Control Room that need to show alerts + warehouse status + task failures on first paint, a single query budget may force you to UNION ALL everything into one ugly mega-query rather than making 3 clean targeted queries.

Metric Semantic Registry suggests you're building toward a semantic layer. This is the right direction, but if the registry isn't connected to a Snowflake Semantic View, you're maintaining two parallel truth-sources. Consider aligning with Snowflake's native semantic model.

The file count went down by 3, but you added 6+ new files. This means you also removed/merged ~9 files. Good. But the net reduction needs to accelerate — at 173 files you're still in "single developer can barely maintain this" territory.

